section.section:
"Chief executive" means:
For Baltimore City, the Mayor;
For a nonhome rule county, the chairman or president of the board of county commissioners;
For a charter county, the elected county executive or, if the county does not have an elected executive, the chairman or president of the county council;
For a code home rule county, the chairman or president of the board of county commissioners;
For a community college, a designee of the board of trustees;
For a municipal corporation, the mayor or, if the municipal corporation does not have a mayor, the chairman or president of the municipal governing body;
For the Washington Suburban Sanitary Commission, the Chairman of the Commission;
For a public corporation, the chief executive officer; and
For an authority, the executive director or executive secretary.

"Governing body" means:
For Baltimore City, the Baltimore City Board of Estimates;
For a nonhome rule county, the county commissioners;
For a charter county, as provided by local law, the county council or the county executive and the county council;
For a code county, the county commissioners;
For a community college, the board of trustees;
For a municipal corporation, the body provided by the municipal charter;
For the Washington Suburban Sanitary Commission, the Commission;
For a public corporation, the board of directors; and
For an authority, the board of the authority.

"Local government unit" means:
Baltimore City;
A community college;
A county;
A municipal corporation;
The Washington Suburban Sanitary Commission;
A public corporation authorized to issue debt; or
An authority of the State authorized to issue debt.

"Public funds" means any revenue held by a local government unit as part of:
A general fund;
A special fund;
A capital improvement fund;
A debt service fund;
An enterprise fund;
An internal service fund; or
Except as otherwise provided in subparagraph (ii) of this paragraph, any other account of the local government unit.

The State Treasurer's local government investment guidelines shall:
State the types of investments in which public funds may be invested;
Include guidance for the prudent investment of public funds based on cash flow projections, income, liquidity, investment ratings, and risk;
Require that investments by a board of education and a board of library trustees are in compliance with the local investment policy of the respective county; and
Prohibit borrowing of funds for the express purpose of investing those funds.
